      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/13edae/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-09-19T08:33:30.381Z",
      "cooked": "<p>insufficient and inconsistent power supply problem I use the Tacx Flux trainer and I noticed that the trainer tends to disconnect or even generate less power than the workout created previously, it seems weakened by 40%, I use a racing bike and even when changing gears the problem remains, for example I have to do 5 minutes at 300 watts it starts by providing a resistance equal to 300 watts but then changes and goes to 220 watts, only by closing the application and reconnecting the roller then it starts working again, and it happens several times during 1 activity, how to solve it? I use Android and Samsung smartphones</p>",
